Search the Library Genesis API by text

libgen_search.Rd

Search the Library Genesis API by text and return results of specified counts and sorted on specified fields.

libgen_search(query, count = 25, search_in = "def", sort_by = "def",
  reverse = FALSE, full_fields = FALSE, fields = c())

Arguments

query

the string to search for.
count

the number of results to return, defaults to 25. If the results length is less than count, will return the whole results.
search_in

restrict your search to one of the following fields:

  • title

  • author

  • series

  • periodical

  • publisher

  • year

  • identifier

  • md5

  • extension

  • def (default:Title, Author, Series, Periodical, Publisher, Year, VolumeInfo)
sort_by

The field by which results are sorted:

  • title

  • author

  • publisher

  • year

  • pages

  • language

  • extension

  • filesize

  • extension

  • def (default: Relevance)
reverse

Only if sort_by field is specified. Default to FALSE, if TRUE, sorts Z-A or 9-0. Notice: if results are sorted by a field and reverse set to FALSE, items with no record on that field will come first.
full_fields

whether returns with full fields (TRUE) or selected fields (FALSE).
fields

Optional, user specified vector of fields to return.

Value

A data frame.
